column5: I flew over the east side of Scugog this afternoon and saw 10 sunken huts and several holes where huts had already been removed.  Tomorrow the holes will be glazed over yet not strong enough to walk on, be careful.
Anyone going to scugog should be VERY careful right now as even seasoned locals have had hut problems this year.  That and the wide opem gap running from the tip of the island to the N shore too...
You all need to come visit us up North here. Over 20" of SOLID ice on Nipissing today.
I'd be especially careful around Scugog. You never know what kind of fine the locals might hit you up with. I hear they are strapped for cash these days!

I was on scugog tuesday aft/night for a few hours. Was out half a km or so in 9 feet of water and had a solid 12 inches of clear ice underneath me. Things must have changed quickly. Was a nice night to be out.
